  "prompt": "What universities does Lakeland Financial recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Lakeland Financial, the parent company of Lake City Bank, typically recruits new graduates from various universities in the Midwest, particularly in Indiana. Some of the universities they have recruited from in the past include:\n\n1. Indiana University\n2. Purdue University\n3. Ball State University\n4. University of Notre Dame\n5. Butler University\n\nAs for the majors they look for, Lakeland Financial seeks graduates with degrees in:\n\n1. Finance\n2. Accounting\n3. Business Administration\n4. Economics\n5. Marketing\n6. Management Information Systems\n\nThese are the primary areas of focus for their recruitment efforts. However, they may also consider graduates from other related fields depending on the specific position and the candidate's skills and experience.\n\nKeep in mind that recruitment preferences can change over time, so it's always a good idea to check Lakeland Financial's career page or reach out to their HR department for the most up-to-date information on their recruitment process and targeted universities and majors.",
